patch available.

  - In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved: io_uring/kbuf: hold io_buffer_list
    reference over mmap If we look up the kbuf, ensure that it doesn't get unregistered until after we're done
    with it. Since we're inside mmap, we cannot safely use the io_uring lock. Rely on the fact that we can
    lookup the buffer list under RCU now and grab a reference to it, preventing it from being unregistered
    until we're done with it. The lookup returns the io_buffer_list directly with it referenced.
    (CVE-2024-35880)

Note that Nessus relies on the presence of the package as reported by the vendor.");
